                        <h2>Understanding Mental Wellbeing</h2>
                        <p>Mental wellbeing is a state of mind where an individual realizes their potential, can cope with the normal stresses of life, can work productively, and is able to contribute to their community. It involves emotional, psychological, and social well-being.</p>

                        <h3>Importance of Mental Wellbeing</h3>
                        <p>Maintaining good mental health is crucial for overall wellbeing. It helps in building resilience, managing stress, and developing healthy relationships. Poor mental health can lead to various issues, including anxiety, depression, and physical health problems.</p>

                        <h3>Tips for Enhancing Mental Wellbeing</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Practice mindfulness and meditation.</li>
                            <li>Engage in regular physical activity.</li>
                            <li>Maintain a balanced diet.</li>
                            <li>Connect with loved ones and build a support network.</li>
                            <li>Seek professional help when needed.</li>
                        </ul>

